gomodel:SYNGO_2896  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: \"Endophilin 2, 3 and Arc Localize to Post-synaptic Sites with GluR1 in Hippocampal Neurons\"\n- \"By contrast, endophilin 2 gold particles were enriched in both the pre- and postsynaptic compartments, and were prominent over the PSD and in the lateral margins of dendritic spines.\"\n- \" Vesicular structures containing endophilin 2 and 3 gold particles were present in both the spine and along microtubules in dendrites\". Experimental description: - Species of neurons not stated in the paper, but traced back to PMID:861729: \"Rat hippocampal neurons in dispersed cell culture\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
